title: API Wrapper Around Postcodes.io
text: API wrapper around postcodes.io - free UK postcode lookup geocoder. package helps find transform information UK administrative geography like postcodes, LSOA, MSOA, constituencies, counties, wards, districts, CCG NUTS. package based exclusively open data provided postcodes.io. PostcodesioR can used data scientists social scientists working geocoded UK data. common task working data aggregating geocoded data different administrative levels, e.g. turning postcode-level data counties regions. package can help achieving many cases changing aggregation geographic data required.

title: API Wrapper Around Postcodes.io
text: package can installed GitHub (developmental version) CRAN (stable). order install PostcodesioR use one following commands:
code: # stable version install.packages("PostcodesioR") # developmental version if(!require("devtools")) {   install.packages("devtools") } devtools::install_github("ropensci/PostcodesioR")

title: API Wrapper Around Postcodes.io
text: Load package typing
code: library(PostcodesioR)

title: Bulk reverse geocoding — bulk_reverse_geocoding
text: Returns nearest postcodes given longitude latitude. Accepts 100 geolocations.

title: Bulk reverse geocoding — bulk_reverse_geocoding
code: bulk_reverse_geocoding(geolocations)

title: Bulk reverse geocoding — bulk_reverse_geocoding
text: geolocations list containing array objects geolocate. least two elements needed.

title: Bulk reverse geocoding — bulk_reverse_geocoding
text: list geocoded data.

title: Bulk reverse geocoding — bulk_reverse_geocoding
text: method requires JSON object containing array geolocation objects POSTed. geolocation object accepts optional radius (meters) limit argument. default 100m 10 respectively. also accepts wideSearch argument.

title: Bulk reverse geocoding — bulk_reverse_geocoding
code: # \donttest{ geolocations_list <- structure( list( geolocations = structure( list( longitude = c(-3.15807731271522, -1.12935802905177), latitude = c(51.4799900627036, 50.7186356978817), limit = c(NA, 100L), radius = c(NA, 500L)), .Names = c("longitude", "latitude", "limit", "radius"), class = "data.frame", row.names = 1:2)), .Names = "geolocations")  bulk_reverse_geocoding(geolocations_list) #> Warning: Bad Request (HTTP 400). # }

title: Nearest outcode — nearest_outcode
text: Returns nearest outcodes given outcode. search based relative distance outcode centroid.

title: Nearest outcode — nearest_outcode
code: nearest_outcode(outcode, limit = 10, radius = 5000)

title: Nearest outcode — nearest_outcode
text: outcode string UK postcode. limit integer. Optional parameter. Limits number postcodes matches return. Defaults 10. Needs less 100. radius integer. Optional parameter. Limits number postcodes matches return. Defaults 5,000m. Needs less 25,000m.

title: Place lookup — place_lookup
text: Lookup place code. Returns available data found. Returns 404 place exist.

title: Place lookup — place_lookup
code: place_lookup(code)

title: Place lookup — place_lookup
text: code string. unique identifier places - Ordnance Survey (OSGB) code.

title: Place lookup — place_lookup
text: list available places. code unique identifier enables records identified easily. identifier persistent LocalTypes except Section Named Road Section Numbered Road. name_1 Name. proper noun applies real world entity. Names prefixed definite article formatted alphabetical sorting, , 'Pennines' 'Pennines, '. name_1_lang Language Name. language type set one name exists E.g. cym (Welsh), eng (English), gla (Scottish Gaelic). name_2 Name (case multiple languages). proper noun applies real world entity. Names prefixed definite article formatted alphabetical sorting, , 'Pennines' 'Pennines, '. name_2_lang Language Name. language type set one name exists E.g. cym (Welsh), eng (English), gla (Scottish Gaelic). local_type Ordnance Survey classification named place represented specific feature. E.g. City, Town, Village, Hamlet, Settlement, Suburban Area outcode postcode district, example, SO15. county_unitary Administrative Area. name County (non-metropolitan Metropolitan), Unitary Authority Greater London Authority administrative area point geometry feature within nearest . county_unitary_type Administrative Area Type. Classifies type administrative unit. district_borough District Borough. name District, Metropolitan District London Borough administrative unit point geometry feature within. district_borough_type Borough Type. Classifies type administrative unit. region name European Region (Government O ice Region) point geometry feature within nearest . country country (.e. one four constituent countries United Kingdom Channel Islands Isle Man) place assigned. longitude WGS84 longitude given Place's national grid reference. latitude WGS84 latitude given Place's national grid reference. eastings Ordnance Survey postcode grid reference Easting 1 metre resolution; blank postcodes Channel Islands Isle Man. northings Ordnance Survey postcode grid reference Northing 1 metre resolution; blank postcodes Channel Islands Isle Man. min/max northings/eastings Minimum Maximum, Northings Eastings. Bounding box Minimum Bounding Rectangle (MBR) roads settlements. Settlements Sections Named Numbered Roads, MBR gives representation extent features snapped real world extent. See https://postcodes.io/docs details.

title: Postcode lookup — postcode_lookup
text: Lookup postcode.

title: Postcode lookup — postcode_lookup
code: postcode_lookup(postcode)

title: Postcode lookup — postcode_lookup
text: postcode string. One valid UK postcode. function case- space-insensitive. one postcode use bulk_postcode_lookup. Scottish postcodes use scottish_postcode_lookup.

title: Postcode lookup — postcode_lookup
text: data frame. Returns available data found. Returns NAs postcode exist (404). postcode Postcode. current ('live') postcodes within United Kingdom, Channel Islands Isle Man, received monthly Royal Mail. 2, 3 4-character outward code, single space 3-character inward code. quality Positional Quality. Shows status assigned grid reference. 1 - within building matched address closest postcode mean 2 - status value 1, except visual inspection Landline maps (Scotland ) 3 - approximate within 50m 4 - postcode unit mean (mean matched addresses postcode, snapped building) 5 - imputed ONS, reference surrounding postcode grid references 6 - postcode sector mean, (mainly PO Boxes) 8 - postcode terminated prior Gridlink(R) initiative, last known ONS postcode grid reference1 9 - grid reference available eastings Eastings. Ordnance Survey postcode grid reference Easting 1 metre resolution; blank postcodes Channel Islands Isle Man. Grid references postcodes Northern Ireland relate Irish Grid system. northings Northings. Ordnance Survey postcode grid reference Easting 1 metre resolution; blank postcodes Channel Islands Isle Man. Grid references postcodes Northern Ireland relate Irish Grid system. country Country. country (.e. one four constituent countries United Kingdom Channel Islands Isle Man) postcode assigned. nhs_ha Strategic Health Authority. health area code postcode. longitude Longitude. WGS84 longitude given Postcode's national grid reference. latitude Latitude. WGS84 latitude given Postcode's national grid reference. european_electoral_region European Electoral Region (EER). European Electoral Region code postcode. primary_care_trust Primary Care Trust (PCT). code Primary Care areas England, LHBs Wales, CHPs Scotland, LCG Northern Ireland PHD Isle Man; equivalent areas Channel Islands. Care Trust/ Care Trust Plus (CT) / local health board (LHB) / community health partnership (CHP) / local commissioning group (LCG) / primary healthcare directorate (PHD). region Region (formerly GOR). Region code postcode. nine GORs abolished 1 April 2011 now known 'Regions'. primary statistical subdivisions England also areas Government Offices Regions fulfilled role. GOR covered number local authorities. lsoa 2011 Census lower layer super output area (LSOA). 2011 Census lower layer SOA code England Wales, SOA code Northern Ireland data zone code Scotland. msoa 2011 Census middle layer super output area (MSOA). 2011 Census middle layer SOA (MSOA) code England Wales intermediate zone Scotland. incode Incode. 3-character inward code following space full postcode. outcode Outcode. 2, 3 4-character outward code. part postcode space. parliamentary_constituency Westminster Parliamentary Constituency. Westminster Parliamentary Constituency code postcode. admin_district District. current district/unitary authority postcode assigned. parish Parish (England)/ community (Wales). smallest type administrative area England parish (also known 'civil parish'); equivalent units Wales communities. admin_county County. current county postcode assigned. admin_ward Ward. current administrative/electoral area postcode assigned. ccg Clinical Commissioning Group. Clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) NHS organisations set Health Social Care Act 2012 organise delivery NHS services England. nuts Nomenclature Units Territorial Statistics (NUTS) / Local Administrative Units (LAU) areas. LAU2 code postcode. NUTS hierarchical classification spatial units provides breakdown European Union's territory producing regional statistics comparable across Union. NUTS area classification United Kingdom comprises current national administrative electoral areas, except Scotland NUTS areas comprise whole /part Local Enterprise Regions. NUTS levels 1-3 frozen minimum three years NUTS levels 4 5 now Local Administrative Units (LAU) levels 1 2 respectively. _code Returns ID Code associated postcode. Typically 9 character code known ONS Code GSS Code. currently available districts, parishes, counties, CCGs, NUTS wards. See https://postcodes.io/docs details.

title: Reverse geocoding — reverse_geocoding
text: Returns nearest postcodes given longitude latitude.

title: Reverse geocoding — reverse_geocoding
code: reverse_geocoding(   longitude,   latitude,   limit = 10,   radius = 100,   wideSearch = NULL )

title: Reverse geocoding — reverse_geocoding
text: longitude string numeric. Needs least three decimal points. latitude string numeric. Needs least three decimal points. limit integer. Limits number postcodes matches return. Defaults 10. Needs less 100. radius integer. Limits number postcodes matches return. Defaults 100m. Needs less 2,000m. wideSearch TRUE FALSE. Search 20km radius, subject maximum 10 results. Since lookups wide area can expensive, created method allow choose make trade search radius number results. Defaults false. enabled, radius limits 10 ignored.

title: Scottish postcode lookup — scottish_postcode_lookup
